What will be the output of the following C code, considering operator associativity?

```c
#include

int main() {
    int x = 15, y = 7, z = 3;

    int temp = z * 3;
    int temp2 = temp + 5;

    y = temp2;
    int result = x;

    printf("%d\n", result);
    return 0;
}
```

